\subsection{Ablation Study of HMC Postulates}
We perform ablations by varying:
- P0 scaling ($d_{\rm mem}\propto \exp(c S_{\rm BH})$ with $c\in\{0.75,1,1.25\}$),
- Scrambling strength (weak vs nominal),
- Gentleness parameter $\varepsilon$.

We report five metrics over 100 runs: residual final entropy, RMSE to ideal Page curve, turnover step, and maximum $g^{(2)}$ deviation. Results are summarized in Table~\ref{tab:ablation}.

